 behind st maurice becomes so narrow that there is only space enough for the bed of the river and a narrow an old tower stands here as if it were guardian to the canton valais which ends at this point and from it we can look across the stone bridge to 
 the on the other side where the canton vaud commences not far from this spot stands the town of bex and at every step can be seen an increase of fruitfulness and verdure it is like entering a 
