 this stream however did not pass near enough to the mill and therefore the was turned by a smaller stream which tumbled down the rocks on the opposite side where it was opposed by a stone and obtained greater strength and speed till it fell into a large basin and from thence through a channel to the 
 this channel sometimes overflowed and made the path so slippery that any one passing that way might easily fall in and be carried towards the mill wheel with frightful rapidity such a catastrophe nearly happened to the young englishman he had dressed himself in white clothes like a man and was climbing the path to the 
 house but he had never been taught to climb and therefore 
